commit.message:
Add explicit dependency on mutex_m on Ruby 3.3

Maybe this will silence the warning that is making CI fail.

Revert "Use git version of minitest on Ruby 3.3"

This reverts commit 600b2c463509318e64cecfb5ea140416d3389d68.

This doesn't work because minitest does not include a gemspec
in the repository.

Use git version of minitest on Ruby 3.3

Otherwise, the minitest used is 5.20.0, which emits a warning
about removal that breaks specs on Ruby 3.3. The issue has
been fixed upstream in minitest, but there has not yet been a new
version released with the fix.
Add Ruby 3.3 to CI and bump actions/checkout to v4
Limit Sequel version on Ruby 1.9 in CI to avoid failure due to bigdecimal
Update README.rdoc

commit.message: Switch from hanna-nouveau to hanna
Bump version to 1.5.1
Fix use with minitest 5.19+ by using Minitest instead of MiniTest as the constant
Stop testing Ruby 2.2 in CI as it no longer works with ubuntu-latest
Move to actions/checkout@v3
Add CI for Ruby 3.2
Test JRuby 9.4 in CI

Add coverage testing

No code changes were needed for 100% line/branch coverage. One
nocov block was added, for a branch that is only taken in an old
version of minitest.
Tighten CI permissions
Test Ruby 3.1 in CI

Run specs in verbose mode on Ruby 3+

Fix verbose warnings in specs.

Remove testing on JRuby 9.1 in CI

Tests pass locally, and last commit passed correctly when run
8 months ago (no code changes since). I have many other projects
testing on JRuby 9.1 using minitest-hooks without problems, so
this doesn't appear to be a problem in minitest hooks. I don't
feel debugging this is a good use of my time, so I'm going to
remove jruby-9.1 from the CI matrix.
Try Ruby 1.9.3, 2.0, and JRuby 9.3 on GitHub Actions
Stop using Travis
Bump copyright year
Start testing Ruby 3.0 in CI, and simplify ci.yml
Update copyright year
Use GitHub Actions CI for supported Ruby versions
Try using trusty for older JRuby to get tests passing on Travis
Try to get Travis passing

Use minitest-global_expecations in tests to avoid deprecation issues with minitest 5.12

Also, force minitest 5.11.3 on ruby <2.4, as minitest 5.12.0
breaks on ruby <2.4.

Also, disable automatic loading of minitest plugins when running tests.
Use older version of ruby-sqlite3 on Travis on Ruby 1.8
